# API GUIDELINES

Source: [`docs/TECHNICAL.md`](docs/TECHNICAL.md) §8–§9, §16. Consult `core.mdc`, `backend.mdc`, `frontend.mdc`.

## Skills (read first)

`cqrs-handler-pattern`, `clean-architecture-rules`, `testcontainers-integration-tests`, `database-performance`

## Scope

`TradingSimulator.Api` — thin HTTP + SignalR. **MediatR only** in handlers; map to `TradingSimulator.Contracts` DTOs — never serialize domain entities.

## Naming

- No XML doc comments; no abbreviations in identifiers (see `core.mdc`).
- Use `AssemblyReference.Assembly` for endpoint discovery.

## SignalR layout

| Location | Responsibility |
|----------|----------------|
| `Contracts/Realtime/` | Hub client interface, group names, message records |
| `Application/Abstractions/Realtime/` | `IRealtimeNotificationPublisher`, `IRealtimeHubConnectionRegistry` |
| `Api/Hubs/SimulationHub.cs` | Connection groups (`market:{symbol}`, `user:{userId}`) |
| `Api/Realtime/SignalRRealtimeNotificationPublisher.cs` | `IHubContext` adapter (implements Application port) |

Hub path: `/hubs/simulation`. Matching engine and handlers depend on `IRealtimeNotificationPublisher`, not `IHubContext` directly.

